{
  "texts": [
    "For cases that fall outside the scope of the Product Liability Directive, producers may still be held liable under national fault-based liability rules in the Member States.",
    "This may be the case for categories of damages that are not covered by the Product Liability Directive, such as non-material damages.",
    "This may affect damages related to fundamental rights caused by defective products, which may be relevant in the context of AI systems.",
    "This is the reasoning for vicarious liability regimes, e.g.",
    "employer liability for the actions of employees."
  ]
}